sequenceDiagram
    participant C as Citoyen
    participant F as Frontend<br/>(CitoyenEditProfil)
    participant Crop as AvatarCropModal<br/>(react-easy-crop)
    participant Ctx as CitoyenAuthContext
    participant Api as citoyenApi
    participant G as API Gateway
    participant U as service-users<br/>(avatarController)
    participant Sharp as Sharp pipeline
    participant FS as storage/avatars
    participant PG as PostgreSQL

    Note over C,F: Sélection + validation côté client

    C->>F: Clic "Changer la photo"
    F->>C: Ouverture file picker (JPG/PNG/WebP, 5 Mo max)
    C->>F: Sélection fichier
    F->>F: Vérif MIME image/(jpeg|png|webp)<br/>+ taille ≤ 5 Mo
    F->>F: FileReader → data URL
    F->>Crop: Ouverture modale de recadrage
    C->>Crop: Recadrage carré + zoom
    Crop-->>F: croppedFile (Blob JPEG)

    Note over F,U: Upload multipart

    F->>Api: POST /users/avatar/upload (FormData)
    Api->>G: Forward (JWT)
    G->>U: Forward (route protégée /users/avatar)
    U->>U: multer.diskStorage<br/>écriture temporaire dans storage/temp
    U->>Sharp: getImageDimensions
    Sharp-->>U: {width, height}

    alt Image < 100x100
        U->>FS: fs.unlink fichier temp
        U-->>G: 400 "Image must be at least 100x100"
        G-->>Api: 400
        Api-->>F: throw err
        F->>C: Affichage erreur
    else Image valide
        U->>FS: deleteOldAvatars(userId)<br/>(supprime original/, thumbnails/, mini/)
        U->>Sharp: processAvatar(userId, file)
        Sharp->>Sharp: resize 1000x1000 → original/<userId>.jpg
        Sharp->>Sharp: resize 200x200  → thumbnails/<userId>.jpg
        Sharp->>Sharp: resize 64x64    → mini/<userId>.jpg
        Sharp-->>FS: 3 fichiers écrits
        Sharp-->>U: urls = {original, thumbnail, mini}
        U->>PG: UPDATE utilisateur SET<br/>avatar_url=$1, avatar_thumbnail=$2,<br/>avatar_mini=$3 WHERE id_utilisateur=$4
        U-->>G: 201 {avatar_url, avatar_thumbnail, avatar_mini}
        G-->>Api: 201
        Api-->>F: response
    end

    Note over F,Ctx: Synchronisation cross-pages instantanée

    F->>Ctx: bumpAvatarVersion() — immédiat
    F->>Ctx: refreshUser() — re-fetch profile-with-stats
    Ctx->>Api: GET /api/users/profile-with-stats
    Api->>G: Forward
    G->>U: Forward
    U->>PG: SELECT userProfileColumns<br/>(inclut avatar_url/thumbnail/mini)
    PG-->>U: profil enrichi
    U-->>G: {data: profile}
    G-->>Api: 200
    Api-->>Ctx: payload
    Ctx->>Ctx: maybeBumpAvatarVersion(prev, next)<br/>(détecte changement chemin avatar)
    Ctx->>Ctx: setUser(merged) + localStorage.set
    Ctx-->>F: state mis à jour

    Note over F,C: Affichage avec cache-bust

    F->>C: <img src=buildAvatarUrl(path, {bust: avatarVersion})>
    Note over C: Le ?t=<timestamp> force le navigateur<br/>à refetch (le filename est stable :<br/>/avatars/thumbnails/<userId>.jpg)

    Note over G,C: Servir l'avatar (public, cross-origin)

    C->>G: GET /avatars/thumbnails/<userId>.jpg?t=...
    G->>U: Forward (publicRoute /avatars/, méthodes GET+HEAD)
    U->>U: middleware override headers<br/>Cross-Origin-Resource-Policy: cross-origin<br/>Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *
    U->>FS: express.static(storage/avatars)
    FS-->>U: bytes
    U-->>G: 200 image/jpeg
    G-->>C: image affichée

    %% Pipeline avatar (architecture isolée du flow admin)
    %% - Filename stable : /avatars/<size>/<userId>.<ext>
    %%   → URL inchangée entre uploads → besoin du cache-bust côté client
    %% - avatarVersion (CitoyenAuthContext) : timestamp partagé bumpé
    %%   à chaque changement de chemin avatar OU appel manuel après upload
    %% - Tous les <img src> citoyens (Home, Profil, EditProfil) passent
    %%   avatarVersion via buildAvatarUrl(path, {bust: avatarVersion})
    %% - CORP=cross-origin sur /avatars pour permettre l'affichage depuis :5173
